cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with extracting dense optical flow from videos using a convolutional neural network, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the network architecture and training process, which are related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions constraining weights within the network, which is a technique used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the representation of motion and dynamic textures, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
